content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1262.38 - Starting of engines while fuel on ground prohibited

State Regulations

In the event of spillage involving aircraft, engines
may not be started until the area has been flushed or cleaned in an equally
effective manner and permission granted to start. Notes
